<HEADLINE>
2007 NATIONAL SPELLING BEE TAKING ENROLLMENTS FOR SEMIFINALS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  May 14 (CNA) 05/14/07  18:16:47 (By Ruth Wang)
</P>
<P>
The 3rd National Spelling Bee, an annual English spelling
competition, has started taking enrollments for semifinal
participants from preliminary winners in elementary, junior high,
senior high and vocational schools, until May 20, a competition
organizar said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Ho Neng-yu, chief executive of the Sayling Wen Cultural and
Educational Foundation, said the spelling competition is modeled
on American spelling bees and aims to improve Taiwanese students'
English competence.
</P>
<P>
According to Ho, the semifinals will be held in Taoyuan June 2,
in Taichung June 3, in Kaohsiung and Taipei June 9 and in the
newly added location of Hualien June 10.
</P>
<P>
No enrollment fees are required this year and there will be
special competitions in Taichung for students from two schools
for the blind, Ho said.
</P>
<P>
The final competition will be held in Taipei Aug. 10, he added.
</P>
<P>
The total amount of this year's prize money is NT$440,000
(US$13,208), the highest in the history of the competition, and
the champions  in each  group will each win NT$80,000  including
scholarships for study tours abroad, or NT$30,000 cash without
the scholarship.
</P>
